{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"usefulItems":"baking paper, serving dish","id":"r156329","imageLink":"https:\/\/3.bp.blogspot.com\/-_Jl9QgNelUo\/XZQwEK0fKRI\/AAAAAAAAciY\/K-tw0VMqKyMejWyx0YqyzlexVB35Sx14QCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_S7dZTYJFIQ38o9bH.png","title":"Bacon-wrapped turkey leg with potatoes","publishedAt":"2017-05-08T00:00:00Z","ingredients":[{"content":"30 g garlic cloves"},{"content":"5 sprigs fresh rosemary"},{"content":"150 g bacon slices"},{"content":"800 g skinless turkey legs"},{"content":"1 tsp salt"},{"content":"3 pinches ground black pepper"},{"content":"20 g extra virgin olive oil"},{"content":"1300 g water"},{"content":"600 g potatoes, cut into pieces (4 cm)"}],"nutrition":{"protein":"51 g","fat":"23 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"26 g","calories":"2174 kJ \/ 520 kcal"},"preparations":[{"content":"Place garlic cloves into mixing bowl and chop <b>5 sec\/speed 5<b>."},{"content":"Place a large sheet of baking paper (approx. 40 cm x 60 cm) onto work surface. Arrange rosemary sprigs on baking paper, then arrange 50 g of the bacon slices side by side. Place turkey leg onto bacon and rub meat with chopped garlic. Season with ½ tsp of the salt and black pepper, then wrap turkey in the bacon on which it is resting and cover with remaining 100 g bacon slices. Drizzle with oil. Fold baking paper to form a parcel, twist ends tightly to retain the cooking juices and place parcel into Varoma dish."},{"content":"Place water and remaining ½ tsp salt into mixing bowl. Place Varoma into position, secure Varom lid and steam <b>50 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<b>. Meanwhile peel and cut the potatoes into pieces (4 cm)."},{"content":"Set Varoma aside. Insert simmering basket into mixing bowl and weigh potatoes into it. Place Varoma back into position, secure Varoma lid and steam <b>30 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<b>. Remove Varoma and check that turkey leg is cooked. If necessary steam a further <b>3-10 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<b> (for every 100 g additional weight of turkey leg, add approx. 3 minutes)."},{"content":"Remove Varoma and carefully open parcel, reserving collected juices. Transfer turkey leg to a serving dish and cut meat into slices. Drizzle cooking juices over turkey slices and serve hot with potatoes."}],"hintsAndTricks":["<i>This dish is as festive as any roast, moist and flavourful, and very easy to prepare. You can enjoy your guests’ company while it steams in the Varoma, and the clean-up after they leave is quick and simple.<\/i>","To make sure a few holes in the Varoma dish remain unobstructed for steam to circulate, you can place the butterfly whisk in the centre of the Varoma dish underneath the meat parcel to raise it off the bottom of the Varoma dish."],"basicInfo":["easy","25m","1h 40m","4 portions"]}